definitions: (of a gas or its container) having artificially raised pressure
shortDefinitions: past and past participle of pressurize

definitions: (of an aircraft cabin) maintained at a tolerable atmospheric pressure at a high altitude

examples.text: pressurized cabins keep the conditions similar to that at the earth's surface

shortDefinitions: (of aircraft cabin) maintained at tolerable atmospheric pressure at high altitude

definitions: (of a person or situation) under considerable psychological or social pressure

examples.text: their ability to perform in a very pressurized environment

shortDefinitions: (of person or situation) subject to considerable psychological or social pressure
